I"x<p>Upon realizing her generation won’t have a future unless the world’s politicians act now on climate change, then 15-year-old Greta Thunberg skipped school in August 2018 to protest outside the Swedish parliament. What started as a one person strike soon gained global momentum.</p>

<p>In ‘Make The World Greta Again’, we follow Greta and the organizers of the school strikes for climate as they are cementing a worldwide movement ahead of their first global protest that took place on March 15th, 2019.</p>

<p>It was the biggest climate strike in history with up to 1.6 million students in more than 125 countries.</p>
